The name Waradgery is believed to be derived from a local Aboriginal word (probably in relation to the Wiradjuri people.

Waradgery County, New South Wales is one of the 141 Cadastral divisions of New South Wales . It contains the town of Hay . It includes the area between the Lachlan River and the Murrumbidgee River where they meet. The Lachlan River is the northern boundary of the county, and the Murrumbidgee for a small section is the southern boundary, but the county also includes some of the land to the south of the Murrumbidgee near Hay.
